Bremelanotide (PT-141) is a melanocortin receptor agonist (primarily MC4R).
Indication: FDA-approved for Hypoactive Sexual Desire Disorder (HSDD) in premenopausal women.
Mechanism: Directly activates MC4R in the brain, bypassing the need for dopamine in the sexual response pathway.
Safety: High incidence of nausea (up to 40%). Potential for increased blood pressure.
Evidence: Large-scale clinical trials (RECONNECT) demonstrated efficacy over placebo for HSDD.
